mployee Payroll User Guide (Role-Based)

1. Workflow Overview
HR (98) -> Finance (36) -> HR (98) -> Generate Salary -> Enable Slip

2. Who Can Do What
Role 98 (HR)
Main stage for editing: stepTrack = 1
Final processing stage: stepTrack = 3
Role 36 (Finance)
Finance verification stage: stepTrack = 2
3. Input Edit Rules (Table)
HR (98)
Editable rows: stepTrack = 1 (and null if present)
Editable fields: Attendance, LWP, Basic Pay, Arrear, Comment, Other Deduction (as per row state)
Not editable: Income Tax
Locked rows: stepTrack = 2/3/4 (or held rows)
Finance (36)
Editable rows: stepTrack = 2
Editable fields: Income Tax, Adv/Oth Ded
Not editable: General HR fields (attendance/basic/etc.)
Locked rows: stepTrack != 2 (or held rows)
4. Hold Checkbox Rules
Disabled for Finance role generally
Disabled for HR when row is at stepTrack = 3
Disabled on locked rows
Enabled for HR on editable step-1 rows
5. Button Behavior (Visible vs Enabled)
Buttons are shown role-wise, but become disabled when conditions are not met.

HR (98) buttons
Save -> enabled when at least one active row is at step null/1
To Finance -> enabled when at least one active row is at step null/1
Back Finance -> enabled when at least one active row is at step 3
Generate -> enabled when at least one active row is at step 3 and not already fully generated
Enable Slip -> enabled only if at least one row has:
stepTrack = 4, and
salaryStatus != "generated"
Finance (36) buttons
To HR -> enabled when at least one active row is at step 2
Back HR -> enabled when at least one active row is at step 2
6. Generate & Slip Notes
Generate confirmation count includes only pending employees (already generated rows are excluded).
Step column shows:
normal step badge
extra Slip Enabled badge when applicable (generated row condition in final step UI).
7. APIs Used in Flow (User-facing actions)
Forward/Save/Generate path: /SalaryGenerate/generate-salary
Send back actions: /SalaryGenerate/salary-send-back
Enable Slip: /SalaryGenerate/salary-slip-generate
Single slip download action is available from Action column.